CatDescriptText: Annie Jones, 306 Jacksonia Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1959, pg. 29 with question: "Do you think that the Wacs and others women's units, with the exception of nurses, should be abolished in armed services during peacetime? Why?" answer reads: "I think that in the majority of the cases the parents rule the home.  There is something drastically wrong when this is not the case."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Annie Jones wearing light colored coat with three buttons, and three strand beaded necklace, standing in front of stone block wall with flecked stone wainscot, with pedestrian and continuation of building facade in background
